properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 11:05AM PST until January 14 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
...ADDITIONAL SNOW EXPECTED MONDAY THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...

.Another round of light to moderate snow accumulations is
expected Monday through Tuesday morning. Snow level elevations
will fluctuate considerably throughout the event, likely from
around 3500 feet Monday afternoon, to as low as 2000 to 2500 feet
by Tuesday morning. Regardless, many local interior highways will
see snow accumulations in higher elevations, including Highways
299, 3, and 36. An additional, much stronger storm will also bring
heavier snow to the region Wednesday and Thursday.

* WHAT...Snow accumulations of 4 to 8 inches possible Monday
through early Tuesday.

* WHERE...Del Norte and Humboldt County Interior above 2500 feet.

* WHEN...From 10 AM Monday to 10 AM Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult, particularly near
high elevation highway summits. The hazardous conditions could
impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels will fluctuate considerably
during this event, ranging from roughly 3500 feet during the
afternoon Monday, to 2500 feet by Tuesday morning. Lowest
elevation snow is expected overnight Monday and Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state of California can be
obtained by calling 1-800-GAS-ROAD.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY ABOVE 2500 FEET
